    "description": "Six Senses India Capital India is actively seeking a talented and motivated Guest Relations Manager to join our dynamic team in Ghaziabad. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Six Senses India Capital India:\nSix Senses India Capital India is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure compliance with FSSAI, health, and safety regulations\n• Handle guest complaints and resolve issues promptly\n• Monitor F&B service quality and maintain hygiene standards\n• Train and supervise front-line staff on service standards\n• Plan and execute banquets, events, and MICE functions\n• Develop and maintain relationships with corporate clients\n• Conduct regular guest satisfaction surveys and implement improvements\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBBS / MD / MS from recognized medical college\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in OTA Management\n• Proficiency in Hotel Management\n• Proficiency in Revenue Management\n• Proficiency in Event Management\n• Proficiency in Barista Skills\n• Proficiency in Food Safety\n• Proficiency in Customer Relations\n• Proficiency in Housekeeping Standards\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Flexible working hours\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Ghaziabad, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Six Senses India Capital India!",
